quran[6]{c,v,t}:
  7,59,"We sent Noah to his people. He said: \"O my people! worship God! ye have no other god but Him. I fear for you the punishment of a dreadful day"
  7,60,"The leaders of his people said: \"Ah! we see thee evidently wandering (in mind)"
  7,61,"He said: \"O my people! No wandering is there in my (mind): on the contrary I am an apostle from the Lord and Cherisher of the worlds"
  7,62,"I but fulfil towards you the duties of my Lord's mission: Sincere is my advice to you, and I know from God something that ye know not"
  7,63,"Do ye wonder that there hath come to you a message from your Lord, through a man of your own people, to warn you,- so that ye may fear God and haply receive His Mercy"
  7,64,"But they rejected him, and We delivered him, and those with him, in the Ark: but We overwhelmed in the flood those who rejected Our signs. They were indeed a blind people"